info.name: MicroPowerManager API docs
info.description:
![MPM Logo](https://micropowermanager.com/assets/images/Website_Illustrations_Logo.png)

Decentralized utility management made simple. Manage customers, revenues and assets with this all-in one open source platform.

--- # 💫 Overview This documentation will provide all the information you need to work with our API. As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile). You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).

item.name: Log the user out (Invalidate the token).

Refresh token
Generates a new valid token for the next 3600 seconds
Inorder to generate the new token, a working (Bearer)token has to be provided in the header.

The response is paginated with 15 results on each page/request.

item.name:
Search
The search term will be searched in following fields
- Tariff.name
- Serial number.

Detail
Detailed meter with following relations
- MeterParameter.tariff
- MeterParameter.owner
- Meter Type
- MeterParameter.connectionType
- MeterParameter.connectionGroup
- Manufacturer.

item.name: Vodacom Transaction
item.description: API endpoints for integrating with Vodacom's M-Pesa payment services

request.description:
Validates a transaction before processing. Use this endpoint to verify if a transaction
can proceed based on the provided information. This is typically the first step in the payment flow.

response.name: Validation Error

request.description:
Processes a previously validated transaction. This endpoint should be called after successful
validation to initiate the payment process with Vodacom M-Pesa.

Checks the current status of a transaction that has been submitted for processing.
Use this to verify if a payment has been completed, is still pending, or has failed.

response.name: Enquiry Error
